cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques applied to bilingual word embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of joint semantic spaces, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning (cs.LG). The authors also use similarity measures and correlations, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the influence of geography and contact on semantic similarity, which could be considered a social impact of technology (cs.SI).
